Common Alert Sources:
SIEM, IDS/IPS, EDR, Firewall, Antivirus

Severity Levels:
Critical = Immediate action required
High = Serious threat
Medium = Suspicious activity
Low = Minor issue
Informational = Monitoring only

Alert Triage Process:
1. Review Alert
2. Validate Alert
3. Investigate Logs
4. Determine Impact
5. Escalate if needed

Important Alert Fields:
Timestamp, Source IP, Destination IP, Username, Event ID, Severity

False Positive = Benign activity detected as malicious
True Positive = Real malicious activity detected

IOC (Indicators of Compromise):
Malicious IPs, Suspicious Domains, File Hashes, Unknown Processes, Failed Login Attempts

MITRE ATT&CK Examples:
T1059 = Command and Scripting Interpreter
T1110 = Brute Force

Incident Reporting Template:
Incident Title
Severity
Date & Time
Affected Host
User
Description
Investigation
Action Taken
Status

SOC L1 Responsibilities:
Monitor Alerts
Analyze Logs
Validate Threats
Create Reports
Escalate Incidents

Best Practices:
Verify alerts properly
Maintain documentation
Reduce false positives
Follow escalation procedures
Maintain investigation timeline

